{
  "texts": [
    "More sophisticated frameworks combine dynamic coverage feedback with static path analysis.",
    "For instance, the Panta framework first statically extracts all linearly independent paths of the program.",
    "Then, in each iteration, based on the current dynamic coverage report, it employs an \"exploitation-exploration\" strategy to select the most promising paths for testing, thereby guiding the LLM to improve coverage more efficiently [57].",
    "Furthermore, dynamic analysis can provide deeper feedback in scenarios such as regression testing.",
    "For example, Mokav [38] not only compares the final outputs of two programTable 4."
  ]
}